On this page

1. Preparation ​

Before using the TIDAL music service, you need a valid TIDAL account.

For first-time login, open TIDAL on your device under "Streaming" - "Music", or open it in the Eversolo Control app under "Discover" - "Music Services". Follow the on-screen prompts to complete login.

2. Log In ​

Please enter your TIDAL account and password on your device or in the Eversolo Control app to log in.

If you haven't created a TIDAL account yet, please click "Sign up" and follow the prompts to complete the account registration.

3. Browsing ​

After successfully logging in, you can browse TIDAL music on your device or in the Eversolo Control app. At the top of the interface, you will see sections for Home, Explore, Releases, TIDAL Rising, TIDAL Masters, My Mix, Playlists, Genres, and My Collection.

You can browse these categories layer by layer to access various recommended content from TIDAL's curated music selection. You can also view your saved playlists, albums, singles, and artists in the My Collection section.

4. Search ​

Click the search box at the top to search the entire TIDAL music library, finding Artists, Albums,Tracks, Playlists, and more to quickly locate your desired music resources.

[Dual-end demonstration of the device and Eversolo Control]

5. More ​

In the browsing interface, you can access the more functions menu by clicking the "" icon to the right of a track or the "" icon in the upper right corner of an album/playlist.

This menu supports the following functions:

More menus for singlesMore menus for albums/playlists
Play now / Play nextPlay all tracks now
Add to the end of play queueAdd all tracks to the next play
Add to device playlistAdd all tracks to the end of the play queue
Favorite to TIDALAdd to device playlist
Add to TIDAL playlistFavorite to TIDAL
View artistAdd all tracks to TIDAL playlist
View album/

Tips:

  • Saved content can be viewed and managed at any time in the "My Collection" section.
  • Content added to your device's playlist can be viewed and managed centrally in My Favorites - Device Playlists.
[Dual-end demonstration of the device and Eversolo Control]

6. Streaming Quality ​

When using the TIDAL music service, you can select the streraming quality mode by clicking the "" icon in the upper right corner of the homepage or by clicking the "" icon on the playback details screen.

Supported options include:

  • Low
  • Medium (128 kb/s)
  • High (320 kb/s)
  • Lossless (CD-Quality)
  • HiRes (Master)
